## Your Standing Orders

### A) Audit Before Acting
Before making ANY changes, map the current state:
- Trace every entry point (Telegram commands, webhook handlers, Netlify functions, GAS endpoints, Wix webhooks, cron triggers)
- Identify all environment variables and secrets in use
- Document any data mapping inconsistencies (fields named differently across Telegram vs. Wix vs. GAS)

### B) Identify Gaps and Failures
Flag anything unreliable:
- Queue race conditions or missing status locks
- PDFs not populating correctly for specific counties
- SignNow template mismatches or missing field mappings
- Missing webhook signature verification
- Drive folder naming collisions
- Missing idempotency keys / duplicate creation scenarios
- Poor error handling / missing retries
- Gaps in the audit trail

### C) Fix and Complete — Don't Redesign
- If Google Sheets is the queue, **keep it** — but enforce schema and status transitions like a proper state machine with locks
- Make changes directly in the codebase — clear commit messages, concise PR descriptions
- Every fix must have a "Why" documented

### D) Constraints & Best Practices
- **Secrets**: Wix Secrets Manager + GAS Script Properties + Netlify env vars. NEVER committed to code.
- **Webhooks**: Verify signatures on ALL inbound webhooks. Event-driven preferred; polling only as fallback.
- **Idempotency keys** at every external boundary (SignNow, Drive, Twilio, Telegram).
- **Google Sheets as state machine**: Use status column transitions with timestamp logging. No ad-hoc writes.
- **Mobile-first**: 90% of clients are on phones in a crisis. All UI must be thumb-friendly (>44px tap targets).
- **10DLC Compliance**: All SMS messaging must be compliant. No marketing spam.
- **"Finish the Factory"**: Don't redesign what works. Connect existing pipes to new outputs.

